<ns3542:section xmlns:ns3542="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.platforms.linux.printing.printing">

<ns3543:title xmlns:ns3543="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Printing</ns3543:title>
	<ns3544:para xmlns:ns3544="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
		The <ns3545:emphasis xmlns:ns3545="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" role="strong">redhat-config-printer</ns3545:emphasis> command invokes the printer configuration wizard. This allows for multiple printers to be configured, using a number of protocols, ranging from printers shared from microsoft windows workstations, to locally connected printers, using either the USB or parallel interface. Not so long ago the default print service on linux was LPD, but has since been replaced with CUPS. 
	</ns3544:para>
	<ns3546:figure xmlns:ns3546="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
		<ns3547:title xmlns:ns3547="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Printer Configuration Wizard</ns3547:title>
		<ns3548:mediaobject xmlns:ns3548="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
			<ns3549:imageobject xmlns:ns3549="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
				<ns3550:imagedata xmlns:ns3550="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" fileref="../../../../../resources/information/platforms/linux/images/redhat_printer_1.jpg" format="JPEG" align="center"/>
			</ns3549:imageobject>
			<ns3551:textobject xmlns:ns3551="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
				<ns3552:phrase xmlns:ns3552="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Printer Configuration wizard (redhat-config-printer)</ns3552:phrase>
			</ns3551:textobject>
		</ns3548:mediaobject>	
	</ns3546:figure>
	<ns3553:para xmlns:ns3553="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
		Dependent on the connection type, various configuration parameters are required. CUPS, for example, requires the printer host (192.168.1.1), as well as the queue name (/printers/lp).
	</ns3553:para>
	<ns3554:figure xmlns:ns3554="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
		<ns3555:title xmlns:ns3555="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Printer Configuration Wizard - CUPS printing</ns3555:title>
		<ns3556:mediaobject xmlns:ns3556="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
			<ns3557:imageobject xmlns:ns3557="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
				<ns3558:imagedata xmlns:ns3558="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" fileref="../../../../../resources/information/platforms/linux/images/redhat_printer_cups.jpg" format="JPEG" align="center"/>
			</ns3557:imageobject>
			<ns3559:textobject xmlns:ns3559="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
				<ns3560:phrase xmlns:ns3560="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">CUPS configuration screen</ns3560:phrase>
			</ns3559:textobject>
		</ns3556:mediaobject>	
	</ns3554:figure>
	<ns3561:para xmlns:ns3561="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
		Once changes have been, made the linux print service has to be restarted via the apply button. To test the connection to the printer, the use of the test page option in the menu is suggested.
	</ns3561:para>
